==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Methionic
<hw>Meth`i*on"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Me</ets>thyl + <ets>thionic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a sulphonic (<it>thionic</it>)
acid derivative of methane, obtained as a stable white crystalline
substance, <chform>CH2.(SO3H)2</chform>, which forms well defined
salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

